  "title": "ACCOUNTS EXECUTIVE",
  "description": "<p>Prestige-Heritage Services Pte. Ltd. (PHS) is an independent corporate services provider established in Singapore in 2019.</p><p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>As a Client Services Executive (Account Management) working from home on a part-time basis, you will manage a portfolio of assigned clients by delivering accurate financial reporting and responsive support. You will ensure client inquiries and requests are addressed promptly and professionally, contributing to client satisfaction and retention.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Prepare clients’ yearly Management Reports, Profit & Loss statements, Trial Balances, Financial Statements, and corporate tax computations accurately to support client financial oversight</li><li>Respond to client inquiries and resolve concerns efficiently, escalating issues to superiors when necessary to maintain high client satisfaction</li><li>Manage multiple client accounts independently, prioritizing tasks to meet deadlines and deliver consistent results</li><li>Perform ad hoc accounting duties as assigned by supervisors to support business needs</li><li>Collaborate with Business Development personnel who serve as the primary client contact, ensuring seamless client service delivery</li><li>Communicate effectively with Mandarin-speaking clients to facilitate clear understanding and service excellence</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>GCE “O” Level or Diploma in accountancy or related field</li><li>Minimum 2 years of relevant experience in client accounting and account management roles</li><li>Strong interpersonal and communication skills with a client-first attitude</li><li>Self-motivated, organized, and results-driven in a fast-paced environment</li><li>Proficiency in Mandarin to engage with Mandarin-speaking counterparts</li></ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 2,
